    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
        "groupType": "editable",
        "title": "Set permissions for SQL accounts",
        "expandable": true,
        "items": [
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "<br />\nThe monitoring SQL user needs to have `VIEW SERVER STATE` and `VIEW ANY DEFINITION` permission to collect telemetry. You can create such a user using the script below:\n```\nUSE master;\nGO\nCREATE LOGIN [telegraf] WITH PASSWORD = N'mystrongpassword';\nGO\nGRANT VIEW SERVER STATE TO [telegraf];\nGO\nGRANT VIEW ANY DEFINITION TO [telegraf];\nGO\n```\n\nFor Azure SQL Database, you require the View Database State permission and can create a user with a password directly in the database.\n\n```\nCREATE USER [telegraf] WITH PASSWORD = N'mystrongpassword';\nGO\nGRANT VIEW DATABASE STATE TO [telegraf];\nGO\n```"
            },
            "name": "SQL permissions prereq text"
          }
        ]
      },
      "name": "Create SQL user accounts"
    },
    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
